<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1184">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/1183c.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the
                                    Treasury</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that this
                            Department has received definite information through its Consular
                            Service that Vera Cruz, Mexico, is now in the hands of insurrectionary
                            forces.</p>
                        <p>In view of the shipments of arms and munitions of war that are likely to
                            be excepted by the President for routing via Vera Cruz, or that have
                            already been so excepted, I have the honor to request that your
                            Department take such action as may be necessary to hold up all shipments
                            which are to enter Mexican territory through that port until this
                            Department can satisfy itself that conditions are such as to warrant
                            forwarding such articles by the route referred to.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>